The health department said 781,941 positive COVID-19 cases have been identified in South Africa. AFP/Georg Hochmuth JOHANNESBURG - South Africa has recorded 3,370 new COVID-19 cases. This brings the total number of cases to almost 782,000. READ: COVID-19: SA reports 88 new deaths Over 722,000 people have already recovered. The death toll has risen by 89 to 21,378. Over half of the recent deaths occurred in the Eastern Cape. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.